source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/vietnamese-style-shrimp-lettuce-wraps-654a642fcfbffe92530de285
time required: 15 minutes
course: main course
servings: 2
---

Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

In a #large microwave-safe bowl{}, mix @shredded carrots{4%oz}, half the @rice wine vinegar{10%tsp}, ½ tsp @white sugar{1/2%tsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}; microwave ~{30%seconds}. Set aside to pickle, tossing occasionally.

Once water is boiling, add @rice noodles{3.5%oz}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{4-6%minutes}. Drain and rinse under cold water until cool; divide between two #serving bowls{}.

Meanwhile, trim and slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Quarter @lime{2}. Trim @baby lettuce{2}; separate leaves. Pick @cilantro{1/4%oz} leaves from stems; discard stems.

Rinse @shrimp{10%oz}* under cold water; pat dry. Drizzle @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a hot #large pan{}. Add shrimp, scallion whites, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, @pepper{}, and as many @Korean chili flakes{1%tsp} as you like. Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp are opaque, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in half the @soy sauce{2%tbsp}, half the @ponzu sauce{12%ml}, 1 TBSP @brown sugar{2%tbsp}, and a splash of water; cook until shrimp are cooked through, ~{1%minute} more. Divide between bowls with noodles.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together remaining ponzu, remaining vinegar, 1 tsp brown sugar, and juice from two lime wedges.

Place lettuce leaves, cilantro leaves, scallion greens, @peanuts{1/2%oz}, pickled carrots (draining first), and remaining lime wedges in separate serving bowls. Serve family style alongside saucy shrimp noodles, with ponzu-lime sauce for dipping and drizzling.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.